---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Billie — Privacy Policy">
	<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-10 px-2 pb-16 pt-4 sm:px-0">
		<header class="space-y-3">
			<p class="tag-pill">Privacy Policy</p>
			<h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-black md:text-4xl">How Billie handles personal information</h1>
			<p class="text-black/75">
				Last updated March 13, 2026. This Privacy Policy explains how Billie, an expense-sharing and receipt-scanning app operated through Spwnd, collects, uses, stores, and shares personal information when you use the Billie mobile app, related websites, and support channels.
			</p>
		</header>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">1. Scope</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				This policy applies to Billie and related product pages hosted on this site. It does not govern third-party services that Billie relies on, such as mobile app stores, Google sign-in, or payment processors, except to describe how those services help us operate Billie.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">2. Information we collect</h2>
			<ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-black/80">
				<li><strong>Account and identity data:</strong> your name, email address, profile image, authentication identifiers, and sign-in method when you register or sign in with Google, email, password, or email verification codes.</li>
				<li><strong>App content:</strong> expenses, settlements, merchants, dates, cities, itemized purchases, categories, notes, friend connections, invite or placeholder participant details, activity history, notification settings, and subscription status.</li>
				<li><strong>Receipt data:</strong> receipt images you upload, extracted text and structured fields, parsing job metadata, and any corrections you make after scanning.</li>
				<li><strong>Information about other people:</strong> names, optional email addresses, and transaction details you add for friends, family members, or offline participants. You are responsible for making sure you have the right to share that information with Billie.</li>
				<li><strong>Device and usage data:</strong> push notification tokens, platform type, approximate service logs, and diagnostic records needed to operate, secure, and troubleshoot Billie.</li>
				<li><strong>Purchase data:</strong> subscription entitlement and status information received from app-store billing flows and RevenueCat. We do not receive your full payment card number.</li>
				<li><strong>Support and communications:</strong> messages, screenshots, bug reports, and attachments you send to us.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">3. How we use information</h2>
			<ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-black/80">
				<li>Provide the Billie service, including account creation, authentication, syncing, expense tracking, friend balances, settlements, and analytics.</li>
				<li>Upload, store, and parse receipt images to generate suggested expense details and itemized splits.</li>
				<li>Enable premium features, verify subscription status, and prevent fraud or abuse.</li>
				<li>Send transactional or service messages, including push notifications about expenses and settlements.</li>
				<li>Maintain security, enforce our Terms of Service, debug issues, and improve reliability.</li>
				<li>Comply with legal obligations and protect the rights, safety, and security of Billie, our users, and others.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">4. AI-assisted receipt parsing</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				If you use receipt scanning, Billie uploads your receipt image to our backend and submits it for AI-assisted parsing so the app can extract merchant, date, category, item, and totals data. That processing may involve OpenRouter and the model providers routed through OpenRouter. Receipt parsing is optional, may be inaccurate, and should be reviewed by you before you rely on it. Do not upload receipts containing information you do not want processed for that purpose.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">5. Legal bases for processing</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				Where applicable, we process personal information on one or more of these bases: to perform our contract with you and provide Billie; with your consent, such as for camera, photo-library, and push-notification permissions; for our legitimate interests in operating, securing, and improving Billie; and to comply with legal obligations.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">6. How we share information</h2>
			<ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-black/80">
				<li><strong>Service providers:</strong> infrastructure, authentication, email delivery, subscription management, push delivery, hosting, and AI-processing vendors that help us run Billie, such as Convex, Better Auth, Google, Resend, RevenueCat, Expo, and OpenRouter or underlying model providers.</li>
				<li><strong>Other Billie users:</strong> expense, settlement, and participant information is visible to the users involved in those records so the service can function.</li>
				<li><strong>Legal or safety disclosures:</strong> when reasonably necessary to comply with law, enforce our terms, or protect rights, property, or safety.</li>
				<li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> if Billie or related assets are involved in a merger, financing, acquisition, reorganization, or sale.</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				We do not sell personal information, and we do not share personal information for cross-context behavioral advertising.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">7. Device storage and local data</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				Billie stores some information locally on your device to keep the app working, including session data, cached queries, queued offline expenses, receipt drafts, and the last registered push token. Local data remains on your device until it is cleared by the app, overwritten, or removed when you uninstall or reset the app.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">8. Retention</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				We keep personal information for as long as reasonably necessary to provide Billie, maintain account records, honor subscriptions, resolve disputes, enforce agreements, and meet legal requirements. Account records, expenses, settlements, receipt images, and related logs are generally retained until deleted by you, removed through account closure, or no longer needed for operational or legal purposes. Backups may persist for a limited period after deletion.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">9. Security</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards designed to protect personal information. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">10. International transfers</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				Billie and its service providers may process personal information in the United States and other countries that may have different data-protection laws than your home jurisdiction.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">11. Your privacy rights</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				Depending on where you live, you may have the right to request access to, correction of, deletion of, or a copy of your personal information, and to object to or limit certain processing. California residents may have rights to know, access, correct, and delete personal information and to receive equal service without discrimination for exercising those rights. EEA, UK, and similar-jurisdiction users may also have rights to withdraw consent and lodge complaints with a supervisory authority.
			</p>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				To make a request, email <a class="underline decoration-black/30 underline-offset-4" href="mailto:hello@spwnd.dev">hello@spwnd.dev</a>. We may need to verify your identity before acting on a request. Authorized agents may also contact us with proof of authority where required by law.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">12. Children</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				Billie is not directed to children under 18, and we do not knowingly collect personal information directly from them for use of the service. If you believe a minor has provided personal information to Billie in violation of this policy, contact us and we will investigate and delete it where appropriate.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">13. Changes to this policy</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the updated version here and revise the last-updated date above. Material changes may also be communicated in-app or by email when appropriate.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-black">14. Contact</h2>
			<p class="text-black/80">
				Questions about this Privacy Policy or Billie data practices can be sent to <a class="underline decoration-black/30 underline-offset-4" href="mailto:hello@spwnd.dev">hello@spwnd.dev</a>.
			</p>
		</section>
	</article>
</Layout>
